00:16:32,458 --> 00:16:34,833
SO THE COURSE RECORD YOU MADE
IN THE S-TWO THOUSAND

266
00:16:34,916 --> 00:16:37,958
COULD BE BEATEN BY AN EIGHT-SIX?
YOU CAN'T BE SERIOUS.

267
00:16:38,041 --> 00:16:39,708
- SERIOUS AS A HEART ATTACK.

268
00:16:39,791 --> 00:16:41,416
IF YOU'RE LOOKING
AT THE DOWNHILL,

269
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,625
THAT EIGHT-SIX IS A
FORCE TO BE RECKONED.

270
00:16:43,708 --> 00:16:46,666
HIS SPEED WAS SOLID AND HIS
CONCENTRATION WAS UNMATCHED.

271
00:16:46,750 --> 00:16:49,333
IT WAS BETTER THAN
I EVER EXPECTED.

272
00:16:49,416 --> 00:16:52,416
IT MAY HAVE JUST BEEN FOR A
SECOND OR TWO, BUT AT ONE POINT

273
00:16:52,500 --> 00:16:54,916
HE ACTUALLY FORCED ME TO GRAB
ON TO THE STEERING WHEEL

274
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:57,458
WITH BOTH HANDS.

275
00:16:57,541 --> 00:17:00,791
- WOW. I GET IT NOW.

276
00:17:00,875 --> 00:17:03,833
I DIDN'T REALIZE
HE WAS THAT GOOD.

277
00:17:03,916 --> 00:17:07,125
- TO WELD THAT AMOUNT OF SKILL
AT THAT YOUNG OF AN AGE,

278
00:17:07,208 --> 00:17:09,458
IT'S A SCARY THING.

279
00:17:19,583 --> 00:17:22,625
- HOW'D HE DO?
- NOT GREAT.

280
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:25,708
- DAMN! MAN, THAT SUCKS, ON THE
SECOND AND THIRD RUNS HE WAS

281
00:17:25,791 --> 00:17:27,708
STILL IMPROVING ON
HIS PERSONAL BEST!

282
00:17:30,500 --> 00:17:31,958
- THIS SUCKS.

283
00:17:36,750 --> 00:17:38,083
- WE NEED TO GET BACK
TO THE CHIEF

284
00:17:38,166 --> 00:17:39,875
AND REPORT THESE RESULTS SOON.

285
00:17:39,958 --> 00:17:43,791
- MMM-HMM. I'M HAVING A HARD
TIME JUST STANDING HERE.

286
00:17:43,875 --> 00:17:46,833
I CAN'T TELL YOU HOW MUCH
I WANNA RACE THAT GUY AGAIN.

287
00:17:53,916 --> 00:17:56,875
- THAT WAS TOO BAD.
- THAT KIND OF THING HAPPENS.

288
00:17:56,958 --> 00:18:00,041
- YOU CAN REALLY HANDLE
YOURSELF OUT THERE.

289
00:18:00,125 --> 00:18:02,458
CAN I SAY ONE THING TO YOU?

290
00:18:02,541 --> 00:18:04,166
I DON'T THINK YOU'RE THE
KIND OF DRIVER

291
00:18:04,250 --> 00:18:06,666
WHO SHOULD STAY ON THIS SIDE OF
THINGS FOR LONG.

292
00:18:06,750 --> 00:18:09,000
IF YOU WANT I COULD INTRODUCE
YOU TO THE PROPER PEOPLE,

293
00:18:09,083 --> 00:18:11,333
GET YOU MOVING ON TO BIGGER
AND BETTER THINGS.

294
00:18:12,916 --> 00:18:15,083
- I APPRECIATE THE
OFFER, SIR.

295
00:18:15,166 --> 00:18:17,833
BUT I STILL HAVE A FEW THINGS
I FEEL LIKE I NEED TO ACCOMPLISH

296
00:18:17,916 --> 00:18:19,541
WHERE I AM RIGHT NOW.

297
00:18:24,375 --> 00:18:27,833
- THAT'S FINE. IT'S NOT LIKE
I CAN FORCE YOU INTO IT.

298
00:18:27,916 --> 00:18:29,500
SEE YA 'ROUND.

299
00:18:33,583 --> 00:18:35,916
- WE STILL HAVE A
LONG ROAD AHEAD.

300
00:18:37,583 --> 00:18:39,708
THERE ARE STILL BETTER
DRIVERS OUT THERE.

301
00:18:43,583 --> 00:18:44,583
- EXCUSE ME.

302
00:18:52,541 --> 00:18:55,333
- BEFORE WE START I SHOULD WARN
YOU MY STYLE IS ORIGINAL AND

303
00:18:55,416 --> 00:18:58,875
COMPLETELY SELF-TAUGHT, SO YOU
WON'T SEE IT ANYWHERE ELSE.

304
00:18:58,958 --> 00:19:02,041
I'LL SHOW YOU BUT I CAN'T
PROMISE YOU THAT YOU WON'T GET

305
00:19:02,125 --> 00:19:04,166
THAT MUCH OUT OF IT.

306
00:19:04,250 --> 00:19:08,000
- GOD ARM'S GONNA LET HIM RIDE
SHOTGUN. GENEROUS MOVE.

307
00:19:08,083 --> 00:19:11,083
- AND SURPRISINGLY ENOUGH
HE ALMOST JUMPED AT THE IDEA.

308
00:19:11,166 --> 00:19:12,541
BETWEEN US, FUMIHIRO,

309
00:19:12,625 --> 00:19:15,375
I WISH IT WAS ME SITTING IN
JOUSHIMA'S PASSENGER SEAT.

310
00:19:15,458 --> 00:19:17,166
- YOU READY TO GO?

311
00:19:17,958 --> 00:19:19,583
- ANYTIME YOU ARE.

312
00:19:22,875 --> 00:19:24,708
- NOW THAT'S A HELL OF
A RARE EXPERIENCE.

313
00:19:24,791 --> 00:19:27,750
I DOUBT ANYONE'S HAD THE
PRIVILEGE FUJIWARA ENJOYING.

314
00:19:27,833 --> 00:19:31,458
HE GETS TO WATCH JOUSHIMA'S
TECHNIQUE UP CLOSE AND PERSONAL.

315
00:19:31,541 --> 00:19:33,333
- Fumihiro: LUCKY HIM.

316
00:19:33,416 --> 00:19:34,791
- THOSE TWO ARE
SIMILAR MORE THAN

317
00:19:34,875 --> 00:19:36,333
EITHER ONE OF THEM MIGHT THINK.

318
00:19:36,416 --> 00:19:40,458
THE IMPACT ON FUJIWARA
COULD BE ENORMOUS.

319
00:19:40,541 --> 00:19:41,708
THE AMAZING THING
ABOUT HIS STEERING

320
00:19:41,791 --> 00:19:45,000
ISN'T THAT HE'S DOES
IT WITH ONE HAND.

321
00:19:45,083 --> 00:19:47,416
YOU NEED TO LOOK AT HOW
HE'S DOING IT, FUJIWARA.

322
00:19:54,583 --> 00:19:57,583
THE BATTLES FOR D
WILL CONTINUE.

323
00:19:57,666 --> 00:19:59,291
YOU NEED TO BURN
EVERYTHING YOU SEE TONIGHT

324
00:19:59,375 --> 00:20:01,125
INTO YOUR BRAIN AND LET IT SCAR.

325
00:20:01,208 --> 00:20:03,458
YOU'RE GOING TO NEED IT.

326
00:20:03,541 --> 00:20:06,666
AND MANY MORE DIFFICULT
BATTLES THAT LIE AHEAD.

327
00:20:06,750 --> 00:20:10,000
YOU'RE GONNA FIGURE OUT
HOW TO USE IT ALL SOMEDAY.

328
00:20:19,875 --> 00:20:22,000
- HERE WE ARE...
- THE THREE OF US...

329
00:20:22,083 --> 00:20:24,000
- LONELY AGAIN.

330
00:20:24,083 --> 00:20:27,666
- ( all groaning )

331
00:20:27,750 --> 00:20:30,208
- YOU KNOW IF I SAW A GIRL
NEAR ANY ONE OF YOU,

332
00:20:30,291 --> 00:20:31,875
I MIGHT DIE FROM THE SHOCK.

333
00:20:31,958 --> 00:20:34,458
- DON'T SAY THAT, BOSS.
WE FEEL BAD ENOUGH.

334
00:20:34,541 --> 00:20:36,541
- WHEN I WAS YOUR AGE I HAD
AT LEAST TWO CHICKS

335
00:20:36,625 --> 00:20:38,041
AROUND ME AT ALL TIMES.

336
00:20:38,125 --> 00:20:40,250
I DIDN'T HAVE A FRIDAY NIGHT
TO MYSELF TILL I WAS TWENTY.

337
00:20:40,333 --> 00:20:41,583
- I WONDER IF ONE OF US EMITS

338
00:20:41,666 --> 00:20:43,291
SOME KIND OF FEMALE-REPELLING
PHEROMONE.

339
00:20:43,375 --> 00:20:45,458
LIKE THE OPPOSITE OF
THOSE COLOGNES.

340
00:20:45,541 --> 00:20:46,583
- MAYBE.

341
00:20:48,083 --> 00:20:50,708
- HEY! WHAT ARE YOU ASSHOLES
LOOKIN' AT ME FOR!

342
00:20:52,541 --> 00:20:55,333
- HEY, LOOK! IT'S TAKUMI!

343
00:20:55,416 --> 00:20:57,833
- SO, WE HEARD YOU
WON ANOTHER BIG RACE!

344
00:20:57,916 --> 00:21:02,291
- YEAH. NOT SO MUCH A WIN.
IT WAS MORE OF A TIE.

345
00:21:02,375 --> 00:21:05,875
- DON'T BE SO MODEST.
A WIN IS STILL A WIN, MAN!

346
00:21:05,958 --> 00:21:07,166
- IF YOU'D BEEN THERE TO SEE IT,

347
00:21:07,250 --> 00:21:08,916
I DON'T THINK YOU'D
BE SAYING THAT.

348
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:11,916
- GOT THE IMPREZA?
WHERE'S THE EIGHT-SIX?

349
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:13,708
- I BLEW THE EIGHT-SIX'S
SUSPENSION AT THE END

350
00:21:13,791 --> 00:21:15,333
OF THE RACE LAST NIGHT.

351
00:21:15,416 --> 00:21:17,208
SHE'S BEIN' REPAIRED
AS WE SPEAK.

352
00:21:17,291 --> 00:21:19,708
- WAIT SO YOU'RE TELLING
ME YOUR FREE TODAY?

353
00:21:19,791 --> 00:21:21,291
- LOOKS LIKE IT.

354
00:21:21,375 --> 00:21:23,375
- THEN CLIMB OFF YOUR THRONE AND
GO FOR A DRIVE WITH US FOR ONCE.

355
00:21:23,458 --> 00:21:26,041
HEY IKETANI, KENJI,
WHAT DO YOU GUYS SAY?

356
00:21:26,125 --> 00:21:27,791
- YEAH. THAT SOUNDS LIKE FUN.

357
00:21:27,875 --> 00:21:30,416
AND MAYBE TAKUMI CAN TEACH
ME SOME OF HIS MOVES.

358
00:21:30,500 --> 00:21:31,833
- HEY, ME TOO.

359
00:21:31,916 --> 00:21:33,791
- AND SINCE WE DON'T HAVE
ANY CHICKS TO TIE US DOWN

360
00:21:33,875 --> 00:21:36,500
WE CAN MAKE THIS A BOYS NIGHT!

361
00:21:36,583 --> 00:21:38,375
- ( all laughing )

362
00:21:38,458 --> 00:21:40,625
- FOUR YOUNG MEN AND NOT
A GIRLFRIEND IN THE BUNCH,

363
00:21:40,708 --> 00:21:41,958
IT'S ALMOST TRAGIC.

364
00:21:42,041 --> 00:21:44,208
- I HOPE THEY CAN PUT AN
END TO THIS DROUGHT SOON.

365
00:21:44,291 --> 00:21:45,583
YOU NEVER LOSE.

366
00:21:45,666 --> 00:21:48,166
- THERE'S NO SECRET.
I JUST TRY TO DRIVE MY HARDEST

367
00:21:48,250 --> 00:21:50,916
NO MATTER WHO I'M UP AGAINST
OR WHERE I AM.

368
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,375
- YOU DOG.

369
00:21:52,458 --> 00:21:54,791
- QUIT ACTIN' LIKE THAT, MAN.
I JUST RACE CARS.

370
00:21:57,541 --> 00:22:01,791
I KNOW IT SOUNDS TOO EASY,
BUT IT'S WHAT WORKS BEST FOR ME.

371
00:22:01,875 --> 00:22:04,833
I STILL HAVE SO MUCH LEFT
THAT I WANT TO ACCOMPLISH

372
00:22:04,916 --> 00:22:07,250
AND THE ROAD AHEAD OF ME
IS GOING TO BE A LONG ONE.

373
00:22:16,583 --> 00:22:19,708
- ( upbeat music playing )

374
00:22:33,791 --> 00:22:35,583
- SHE'S ALL FIXED UP?

375
00:22:35,666 --> 00:22:39,083
- YEP, I GOT HER
BACK LAST NIGHT.

376
00:22:39,166 --> 00:22:40,541
- GOOD.

377
00:22:44,208 --> 00:22:45,916
HERE YA GO.

378
00:22:49,583 --> 00:22:51,916
- SEE YA LATER, DAD.
- YEAH.

379
00:22:56,541 --> 00:23:01,250
HMM. I DON'T CARE WHAT HE SAYS
HE LOVES DRIVING THAT THING.

380
00:23:01,333 --> 00:23:02,833
I CAN TELL.

381
00:23:05,333 --> 00:23:07,291
- ( yawning )

382
00:23:17,583 --> 00:23:21,000
- YOU'RE AN EXCELLENT DRIVER
BUT STILL ISN'T EVERYTHING.

383
00:23:21,083 --> 00:23:23,250
AND IT'S UNBELIEVABLY
HARD TO MAINTAIN

384
00:23:23,333 --> 00:23:26,291
ONCE YOU DECIDE YOU'RE TOO
GOOD TO PRACTICE.

385
00:23:31,583 --> 00:23:33,875
IF YOU DON'T HAVE
YOUR EYES FORWARD,

386
00:23:33,958 --> 00:23:36,125
CONSTANTLY LOOKING AT
WHERE YOUR HEADED,

387
00:23:36,208 --> 00:23:38,791
YOU'RE NEVER GOING TO
REACH THE NEXT LEVEL.

388
00:23:40,541 --> 00:23:42,791
AND IF YOU ASK ME
THAT A BIG PART

389
00:23:42,875 --> 00:23:46,291
IT TAKES TO BECOME A MASTER.

390
00:23:46,375 --> 00:23:48,083
ME. I'M OLD NOW,

391
00:23:48,166 --> 00:23:51,541
THE BEST I CAN DO IS
MAINTAIN WHAT I HAVE.

392
00:23:54,833 --> 00:23:56,833
BUT YOU'RE STILL YOUNG, KID,

393
00:23:56,916 --> 00:23:58,458
YOU CAN AIM HIGHER.

394
00:23:58,541 --> 00:24:01,416
AND YOU SHOULD, EVERY DAY.

395
00:24:04,958 --> 00:24:08,458
EVEN IF YOU CAN ONLY TAKE AWAY
THE SMALLEST IDEA ABOUT

396
00:24:08,541 --> 00:24:11,208
WHAT I DO FROM RIDING
SHOTGUN WITH ME TODAY,

397
00:24:11,291 --> 00:24:13,250
I'LL BE VERY HAPPY WITH THAT.

398
00:24:13,333 --> 00:24:15,250
IT'LL MEAN THAT YOU
AND I MEETING EACH OTHER

399
00:24:15,333 --> 00:24:17,958
HAD MORE THAN A
LITTLE SIGNIFICANCE.

400
00:24:21,541 --> 00:24:22,875
- I KNOW YOU'RE BEATING
YOURSELF UP

401
00:24:22,958 --> 00:24:24,875
BECAUSE YOU THINK YOU LOST IN
TERMS OF TECHNIQUE,

402
00:24:24,958 --> 00:24:27,583
BUT IN THE END YOU WON THE
BATTLE. AND THAT'S WHAT MATTERS.

403
00:24:27,666 --> 00:24:29,583
TAKE EVERYTHING YOU
LEARNED WITH YOU.

404
00:24:29,666 --> 00:24:31,916
ISN'T LIKE YOU NEED TO KNOW
ALL THE ANSWERS NOW.

405
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:35,250
YOU'RE STILL GROWING, YOU KNOW.
YOU AND PROJECT D.

406
00:24:35,333 --> 00:24:40,458
- WHAT RYOSUKE SAID WAS RIGHT.
HE'S ALWAYS RIGHT.

407
00:24:40,541 --> 00:24:42,000
- Ryosuke: YOU NEED TO BURN
EVERY YOU SEE TONIGHT

408
00:24:42,083 --> 00:24:44,208
IN YOUR BRAIN AND LET IT SCAR.

409
00:24:44,291 --> 00:24:45,541
YOU'RE GONNA NEED IT,

410
00:24:45,625 --> 00:24:48,500
THERE'S MANY MORE BATTLES
THAT LIE AHEAD.

411
00:24:48,583 --> 00:24:51,916
AND WHEN THE TIME COMES ALONG
YOU'LL BE READY.

412
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:54,958
- THERE'S STILL A LOT OF
OBSTACLES TO OVERCOME.

413
00:24:55,041 --> 00:24:57,000
TOO MANY TO COUNT.

414
00:24:59,750 --> 00:25:02,958
BUT I'M GOING TO GET
PAST THEM, ONE AT A TIME,

415
00:25:03,041 --> 00:25:05,833
IN MY EIGHT-SIX.
